,Recommended,293340,14458716,"Posted: 13 February, 2015",all,Rick,"The Good Life is a rare type of game, fitting a very specific interest. However, for those of us with that interest, this game is a gem. The Good Life has its ups and downs, but for the most part it is a very enjoyable game, if it's what you're looking for.Pros :-Huge world to explore, plenty to see and discover-Plenty of missions-Pretty environments-(sometimes) fun minigames-Awesome soundtrack-Good Price-New, rare genre-Online highscore ranking-Great to relax withCons:-The diving is fun, but the camera/player is insanly hard to control-Cheesy intro-Random forced missions while transporting people (rescuing people, taking pictures, running from pirates)-Sometimes you can't save, forcing to lose data or play until the option re-appears.-Long over-complicated 'controls' help on Main Menu-Little interaction with anyone, it gets lonely in such a huge worldOverall, I love this game. If you can look past the downsides it's great. The game is much less 'relax vacation simulator' as I assumed, and more of a 'relaxed small business game, in a vacation area', as you rarely leave your boat/work. However, I think this game is 100% worth the effort. When it goes on sale, the price is perfect (5$). If the devs continue to support this game by fixing bugs and adding new content, this game could be nearly perfect too. Overall, 7/10."
