76561198045774472,Recommended,293340,15836930,"Posted: 15 May, 2015",all,MaRkV,"I have only been playing four hours as I write this but I think this is a ""keeper"". Some people have complained about the boat controls and how hard ""parking"" them is. I have been around boats most of my life. They DO NOT handle like cars. You need to think ahead and this is how they are modeled in the game. Think ahead, realise you do not stop by just throttling back, and you will be berthing your boat neatly before you know it.There have been complaints that the game sells itself as a ""tycoon"" type game. These may be issues that were in the older versions; I don't know about that as I have only just got the game. All I can say is that you have to make sure you have enough cash to keep your business ""afloat"" at all times. I learned that there is no overdraft facility by paying for my repairs, leaving me cashless. Keep a check on your bank balance!So, do I enjoy the game? Yes. The music in the diving area is calming... For a while then I got annoyed with it, sorry bout that. :( I found that the controls for diving are harder to get a hang of than the boats. But then I have never been diving, perhaps they are fine if you have dived, bit like the boat controls maybe? :)The pirates are a bit odd; another review says they are firing nerf darts at you. Couldn't have put it better myself. So far, even my rickity old startup taxi could avoid them so not sure, at this point, what they are there for. I may regret saying that and maybe there will be a dozen waiting for me when I play next time. I do have a very nice boat now, wouldn't want to lose it or get the green paint scratched.It is in the sale, (should that be sail ;-) ) at the moment; buy it now!"
,Recommended,293340,13073770,"Posted: 24 November, 2014",all,Dr. Arbitrary,"I really wanted to like this game. It's a budget title so I went in with what I think are fair expectations. The problems are fixable so I'll start with the good, end with the bad. Maybe they'll get fixed! Edit: The developers have noted that they're working on some of the negatives in my reveiw. This game is NOT shovelware, it's just rough. It's November now, if you're reading this review a few months from now, check the forums to see if my concerns have been fixed. Edit2: Pirate issues have been addressed. I can safely give this game a thumbs up. It's ROUGH, but still good if you like this kind of game.The graphics are a mixed bag, the models for people are so bad, but it's not really a big deal because the game is about boats, water and scenery. I think they did a pretty good job on that although there is definitely some improvement with weather effects.I really liked the physics for waves. You can't just point your boat in a direction and go, you've got to be active on the helm like in a real boat.The controls for everything except steering your boat are awful. Trying to aim when throwing life rings is nauseating. Trying to use the diving controls is a nightmare, fishing is confusing and unfun even once you know what you're supposed to do.The random event generator is unbalanced, a random Hurricane is awesome. Two in a row is dumb.Pirates, at least early in the game are a death sentence. I got two pirate events in a row before giving up on this game.Edit!!: Boat Damage has been addressed and fixed---Boat damage is economically crippling. A trip taking about 10 minutes might pay for 10% of your ship's damage. A single crash can cause that much, pirates might cause 50% damage. Damage also slows you down so good luck earning your way back to 100% health after a pirate hits you.Edited on 25 Nov 2014: Made a note that the developer has acknowledged some of these problems.Edit: 26 Nov 2014: Repair damage has been rebalanced and pirate areas are now marked. This was the thing that made me feel like the game was unplayable. The other issues are still being worked on."
